{
  "texts": [
    "These strategies are compared using the same insertion-based graph structure that exploits RND pruning since this is the best baseline from the results in Section 4.2.",
    "We run 100 queries for each strategy on the Deep and Sift datasets with sizes 25GB, 100GB, and 1B.",
    "We extrapolate the results to 1M queries and report the number of distance calculations to achieve a 0.99 accuracy in Figure 6.",
    "We observe that SN and KS are the most efficient strategies across all scenarios, while SF and MD are the least efficient overall.",
    "The KD strategy is competitive on 25GB and 100GB Deep and Sift datasets but its performance deteriorates on billion-scale datasets."
  ]
}